The Threat to Your Business

THE DECK IS STACKED AGAINST YOU

The independent HVAC contractor is under attack from every angle. None of them do better work than you. They just buy at a scale you were never meant to compete with alone.

01

Private Equity Roll-Ups

Wall Street is acquiring independent contractors market by market, consolidating operations, and using volume pricing to push you out. This isn't a trend. It's a takeover.

02

Big-Box Pricing

Home Depot and Lowe's move equipment at razor-thin margins backed by billion-dollar supply chains. You're not losing on skill. You're losing on cost of goods.

03

National Chains

They spend more on a single ad campaign than most independents gross in a year. They're buying your customers before those customers ever hear your name.

04

You're Buying Alone

Every time you order equipment, parts, or supplies as a single operator, you're paying the highest price on the sheet. That's not a business strategy. That's a disadvantage.

How We Fight Back

ONE CONTRACTOR IS A CUSTOMER.
HUNDREDS OF CONTRACTORS ARE A FORCE.

American Trade Group is a group purchasing organization built exclusively for independent HVAC contractors. We combine the buying power of hundreds of owner-operators into a single negotiating block. Same major brands. Dramatically better pricing. You stay independent. You just stop paying independent prices.

REAL MONEY BACK IN YOUR POCKET.

What Members Get

EVERYTHING THE BIG GUYS HAVE.
NOTHING THEY CAN TAKE FROM YOU.

Equipment Pricing

Major brand equipment at group-negotiated rates. Carrier, Lennox, Trane, Goodman, Daikin, Rheem. The names your customers trust, at prices that actually let you make money.

Parts & Supply Discounts

Refrigerant, copper, filters, motors, controls. The stuff that eats your margins every single day. We negotiate it in bulk so you stop bleeding on every service call.

Business Services

Fleet programs, insurance, software, uniforms, financing. We're building out new vendor partnerships daily with one goal: eliminate every operational cost where you're overpaying because you're buying as a company of one.

Your Independence

No franchise agreement. No brand takeover. No territory restrictions. Your name stays on the truck. Your reputation stays yours. We just make sure you can afford to keep building it.

SIMPLE, HONEST PRICING

We aren't a software company. We're a trade group. Our goal is to save you money, not charge you more of it.

Common Questions

FREQUENTLY ASKED

What does it cost to join?

Nothing. Membership is free. No dues, no fees, no percentage of your savings. We negotiate vendor partnerships that fund the organization. You just save money.

Do I have to change brands or suppliers?

No. We work with the major manufacturers you already trust. You're not switching. You're just paying less.

Is there a contract or commitment?

No. Join when you want. Leave when you want. We keep members by delivering value, not by locking you in.

How is this different from a co-op or franchise?

You keep complete independence. No brand requirements, no territory limits, no royalty fees. We aggregate purchasing volume to negotiate pricing. That's it.

Who qualifies?

Licensed independent HVAC contractors in the United States. Owner-operators, small shops, family businesses. If you're not owned by private equity or a national chain, you're who we built this for.

How fast can I start saving?

Most members access group pricing within 48 hours of verification. The savings start on your next order.
